net.sf.mmm.util.query.api.feature

Interface FeatureFetch<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the generic type of the entity to fetch.
    All Superinterfaces:
    StatementFeature
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    JpqlSelectStatement<E>, OrientDbSelectStatement<E>, SelectStatement<E,SELF>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSelectStatement, JpqlSelectStatementImpl, OrientDbSelectStatementImpl

    public interface FeatureFetch<E>
extends StatementFeature
    A FeatureFetch is for a regular SelectStatement to fetch and retrieve results.
    Since:
    8.0.0
    Author:
    hohwille
    See Also:
    SelectStatement

    • Method Detail

      • query

        ListQuery<E> query()
        Returns:
        a ListQuery to fetch all matching results with a regular SELECT.

      • fetch

        default List<E> fetch()
        Executes this query to fetch all matching results.
        Returns:
        the List with all matching results. Will be an empty List if no results are found.

      • queryFirst

        SingleQuery<E> queryFirst()
        Returns:
        a SingleQuery to fetch the first matching results with a SELECT.

      • fetchFirst

        default E fetchFirst()
        Executes queryFirst() and returns the result.
        Returns:
        the first matching result or null if no result is found.

      • fetchFirstRequired

        default E fetchFirstRequired()
                      throws ObjectNotFoundException
        Executes queryFirst() and returns the result.
        Returns:
        the first matching result.
        Throws:
        ObjectNotFoundException - if the query had no match.

      • queryOne

        SingleQuery<E> queryOne()
        Returns:
        a SingleQuery to fetch a single unique matching result with a SELECT. The Query execution will fail with an exception if it matches multiple result objects. It can only have a single or an empty (null) result.

      • fetchOne

        default E fetchOne()
        Executes queryOne() and returns the result.
        Returns:
        the unique result or null if no result is found.

      • fetchOneRequired

        default E fetchOneRequired()
                    throws ObjectNotFoundException
        Executes this query to fetch a unique result.
        Returns:
        the unique result.
        Throws:
        ObjectNotFoundException - if the query had no match.

      • queryCount

        NumberQuery<Long> queryCount()
        Returns:
        a NumberQuery to fetch the number of matching objects with a SELECT COUNT.

      • fetchCount

        default long fetchCount()
        Executes queryCount() and returns the result.
        Returns:
        the number of objects (rows) matching this query.
